<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/447452-i-wanted-to-know-if-there-is-any">I wanted to know if there is any difference between Cosmos and The Pale Blue Dot. I have just finished reading Cosmos and I was so impressed that I started searching for a new Carl Sagan book when I stumbled onto this. I know about the famous &quot;Pale Blue Dot&quot; speech by Carl. I read the description of the book and I kind of have the feeling that it is more or less the same as Cosmos. Should I go for it?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_447452'><a id="like_count_community_question_447452" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/447452?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">2 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F61663.Pale_Blue_Dot">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/447452-i-wanted-to-know-if-there-is-any">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/447452-i-wanted-to-know-if-there-is-any">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/7646688-christopher-griffen"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1626758698i/7646688._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/7646688-christopher-griffen">Christopher Griffen</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">&quot;Cosmos,&quot; as I remember it, is a rather scientific guide to astronomy and planetology. &quot;Pale Blue Dot&quot; has a much broader scope and a great deal more <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">"Cosmos," as I remember it, is a rather scientific guide to astronomy and planetology. "Pale Blue Dot" has a much broader scope and a great deal more exploratory topics. From terraforming to the future of humanity as a species. I think it makes a nice companion to "Cosmos."<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

