<div id="review_33323662" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/33323662" />
    <a title="Ben" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32419-ben"><img alt="Ben" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1598735066p2/32419.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/33323662?book_show_action=true">Sep 19, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ben" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ben" href="/user/show/32419-ben">Ben</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32419-ben?shelf=science_and_technology">science_and_technology</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer33323662" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8428935309734482965">I recently came across several references to this book while reading the superb <i>God Delusion</i>. I was intrigued, and since it had been quite a while since I read <i>Cosmos</i>, I decided to give Carl Sagan another go.<br/>Besides his beautiful evocative descriptions of moons and worlds in our own Solar system, Sagan gave us a surplus of inspirational and cautionary passages in this work which--even as an adult--make you want to grow up to be an astronaut.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


