<span id="freeTextContainer443129729540433166">Inspirational.<br/>As Oscar Wilde once said: &quot;we are all in the gutter, but some of us are looking at the stars&quot;.<br/>Carl Sagan is one of those thought leaders who direct our sights and aspirations to the best of what humankind can potentially achieve, and inspires us to find the courage to ask the deeper questions, and to nurture our willingness to embrace &quot;what is true rather than what feels good&quot;.</span>
  <span id="freeText443129729540433166" style="display:none">Inspirational.<br />As Oscar Wilde once said: "we are all in the gutter, but some of us are looking at the stars".<br />Carl Sagan is one of those thought leaders who direct our sights and aspirations to the best of what humankind can potentially achieve, and inspires us to find the courage to ask the deeper questions, and to nurture our willingness to embrace "what is true rather than what feels good".</span>
