          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3592451236" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16476173566910289355">Even though this book was written in 1994 it&apos;s still highly relevant today. We have learnt a lot more about the planets since then with the numerous Mars rovers, the Cassini mission to Saturn and other missions way out as far as Pluto. Advances in space based telescopes have told us that exoplanets are very common, in fact most stars seem to have them. Back when this was written it was only a theory that other stars would have planets. I found myself wondering what Carl would have written if he </span>
  <span id="freeText16476173566910289355" style="display:none">Even though this book was written in 1994 it's still highly relevant today. We have learnt a lot more about the planets since then with the numerous Mars rovers, the Cassini mission to Saturn and other missions way out as far as Pluto. Advances in space based telescopes have told us that exoplanets are very common, in fact most stars seem to have them. Back when this was written it was only a theory that other stars would have planets. I found myself wondering what Carl would have written if he were still alive today and privy to this new knowledge.<br /><br />There are lot's of memorably quotes in this book so I am not going to list any of them here. They can easily be found in other places.<br /></span>
